        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 5:39PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>Showers and embedded thunderstorms will continue to shift east
across parts of Lee, Ogle, Boone, McHenry, and NW DeKalb Counties.
Conditions are favorable for funnel clouds with these showers. In
rare occasions, these funnel clouds can briefly reach the ground as
a weak landspout tornado. If they occur, these type of landspouts
tend to weak, brief, and tend to produce minimal damage. Movement
was east at 25 mph.

If threatening weather approaches, seek shelter indoors.

Locations impacted include...

Amboy, Lindenwood, Fairdale, Ashton, Kings, Chana, Harvard, Hebron,
Franklin Grove, Hillcrest, Nachusa, Garden Prairie, Chemung, Eldena,
Greenwood, Kirkland, Davis Junction, Lee Center, Rochelle, Woodhaven
Lakes, Monroe Center, Marengo, Belvidere, Richmond, and Wonder Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
